// =============================================================================
// main_compiler.seen -- Bootstrap compiler driver (Stage 5 orchestrator)
// =============================================================================
//
// This is the entry point for the "compile" subcommand used during bootstrap
// and production builds. It orchestrates the full compilation pipeline:
//
//   Source (.seen) -> Frontend (lex/parse/typecheck) -> Multi-module IR gen
//     -> opt -O3 (per-module, parallel) -> opt --thinlto-bc -> clang -flto=thin
//
// Key design decisions:
//   - Fork-parallel IR generation: each uncached module is compiled in a forked
//     child process. The child inherits a copy-on-write snapshot of the parent's
//     Pass 1 declaration registry, avoiding costly serialization.
//   - Content-addressed IR cache (v3 key = declarationsHash + moduleSourceHash):
//     deterministic IR means the same source + declarations always produce the
//     same optimized object file, enabling cross-stage cache reuse.
//   - ThinLTO linking: per-module bitcode with summaries enables LLD to perform
//     cross-module inlining at link time without the memory cost of full LTO.
//
// Module-level global flags use Int instead of Bool due to a Stage1 codegen
// limitation where boolean variables generate invalid IR.

